.TH "e1000_get_link_up_info_ich8lan" 9 "e1000_get_link_up_info_ich8lan" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
e1000_get_link_up_info_ich8lan \- Get current link speed and duplex
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" e1000_get_link_up_info_ich8lan
.BI "(struct e1000_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 *speed "  ","
.BI "u16 *duplex "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "speed" 12
pointer to store current link speed
.IP "duplex" 12
pointer to store the current link duplex

Calls the generic get_speed_and_duplex to retrieve the current link
information and then calls the Kumeran lock loss workaround for links at
gigabit speeds.
